  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">If the ordered pair <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x comma y\"></span></span> satisfies the system of equations above, what is one possible value of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> ?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [],
  "keys": [],
  "rationale": "<p class=\"direction_paragraph \">The correct answer is either 0 or 3. For an ordered pair to satisfy a system of equations, both the <span class=\"italic\">x</span>- and <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-values of the ordered pair must satisfy each equation in the system. Both expressions on the right-hand side of the given equations are equal to <span class=\"italic\">y</span>, therefore it follows that both expressions on the right-hand side of the equations are equal to each other: <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared, minus 4 x, plus 4, equals, 4 minus x\"></span>. This equation can be rewritten as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared, minus 3 x, equals 0\"></span>, and then through factoring, the equation becomes <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x times, open parenthesis, x minus 3, close parenthesis, equals 0\"></span>. Because the product of the two factors is equal to 0, it can be concluded that either <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 0\"></span> or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x minus 3, equals 0\"></span>, or rather, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 0\"></span> or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 3\"></span>. Note that 0 and 3 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.</p>\n",
